# Virtual Hosts üè¢

Define a site.

```nginx
server {
    listen 80;
    server_name example.com;
    root /var/www/example;
}
```
Nginx picks the block where `server_name` matches the Host header.

# Passing the Torch üî¶

Pass requests to a backend app (like Node.js on port 3000).

```nginx
location / {
    proxy_pass http://localhost:3000;
    proxy_http_version 1.1;
    proxy_set_header Upgrade $http_upgrade;
    proxy_set_header Connection 'upgrade';
    proxy_set_header Host $host;
}
```

# Lightning Fast ‚ö°

Nginx is much faster at serving images/CSS than Node/Python.

```nginx
location /images/ {
    root /var/www/media;
}
```
It uses the kernel's `sendfile` system call for zero-copy speed.

# Upstreams ‚öñÔ∏è

Define a group of servers.

```nginx
upstream backend_servers {
    server 10.0.0.1;
    server 10.0.0.2;
    server 10.0.0.3;
}

server {
    location / {
        proxy_pass http://backend_servers;
    }
}
```
Default is Round Robin.

# HTTPS üîí

Enable secure connections.

```nginx
server {
    listen 443 ssl;
    server_name example.com;

    ssl_certificate /etc/nginx/ssl/cert.pem;
    ssl_certificate_key /etc/nginx/ssl/key.pem;
}
```
Use **Certbot** to auto-generate these.

# Full Config Block üíª

<!-- FULL_CODE_START
server {
    listen 80;
    server_name myapi.com;

    # Redirect all HTTP to HTTPS
    return 301 https://$host$request_uri;
}

server {
    listen 443 ssl;
    server_name myapi.com;

    ssl_certificate /path/to/fullchain.pem;
    ssl_certificate_key /path/to/privkey.pem;

    location / {
        proxy_pass http://localhost:8080;
    }
}
